From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] net: ps4_mts v87 - Orbis unconditional tail + RF diagnostic

After v86 confirmed C45 SMI works and PLL was already on, the four AI
research agents (hermes/glm/kimi/deepseek) ran a parallel Ghidra dig
on Orbis to find what's still missing.

Convergent findings:

1. **deepseek**: partner's reg 5 = 0xc5e1 has BIT 13 SET = REMOTE FAULT.
   The partner is actively rejecting our PHY's signal at the AN protocol
   level.  This explains the infinite AN-complete -> AN-incomplete cycle:
   we get partner's ACK so BMSR bit 5 sets briefly, but partner keeps
   RF=1 in every base page, so the kthread restarts AN, repeat.

2. **kimi**: we've been skipping Orbis's "unconditional tail" of
   mts_mac_init that runs AFTER the efuse-gated block.  Five C45 writes:
     - MMD 0x1e reg 0x189 = 0x110
     - MMD 0x1e reg 0x122 = 0xffff
     - MMD 0x1f reg 0x268 = 0x07f4
     - MMD 0x07 reg 0x03c = 0
     - MMD 0x1e reg 0x330 clear bit 0x1000
   Plus C22 ANAR (reg 4) &= 0xf3ff (clear bits 10-13).
   Plus BAR+0x04 R/M/W &= 0x7fffcfff (clear bits 8-9, 12-13) TWICE.
   These all happen unconditionally on every Orbis boot.  v82-v86
   skipped them.

3. **glm + gpt5.5** confirm: no PMA/PCS (MMD 1/3) writes anywhere,
   no force-link, no master/slave manipulation.  Interface mode is
   already RGMII via parent prelude's BAR+0x11c &= 0xf8ff.  But Orbis
   does NOT set RGMII delay (MMD 0x1e regs 0x13/0x14) - mainline mtk-ge
   does, suggesting the MT7531's silicon defaults may be wrong without
   it.

This patch implements convergent action items 1 + 2:

  - Adds the 5 C45 unconditional tail writes at end of mts_mac_init
  - Adds C22 ANAR &= 0xf3ff
  - Adds BAR+0x04 R/M/W &= 0x7fffcfff (twice, per Orbis)
  - Adds final BMCR |= 0x1200 AN restart inside mac_init (Orbis order)
  - kthread now reads PHY reg 5 (LP ABILITY) and reg 10 (1000BT status)
    every iteration and logs on change.  This will show:
      * Whether partner RF flag (reg 5 bit 13) toggles per iteration
        (would mean it's transient, not stuck)
      * Whether M/S config fault (reg 10 bit 13) is set
  - REMOVES periodic AN restart (every 15s).  Now only on first
    iteration OR UP->DOWN transition.  Lets PHY complete AN naturally
    and lets deepseek's RF hypothesis play out.

Pass criteria:

  - dmesg shows "v87 tail: MMD 0x1e reg 0x330 0x???? -> 0x????"
  - dmesg shows "v87 tail: ANAR 0x???? -> 0x???? (mask 0xf3ff)"
  - dmesg shows "v87 tail: BMCR 0x???? -> 0x????"
  - phy_ctrl: LP ABILITY (reg5)=0xc5e1 (RF=1 ...) - confirms RF state
  - phy_ctrl: 1000BT_STAT (reg10)=0x???? - shows M/S config
  - No more 15s AN restart cycle in dmesg (only iter=0 and transitions)
  - If link comes up: tail writes were the missing piece
  - If link still down BUT reg 5 stays at 0xc5e1 with RF=1 forever:
    confirmed partner-rejection hypothesis -> v88 will try stop
    advertising 1000BT (reg 9 = 0x0000)
  - If RF flips to 0 occasionally: it's a transient, AN may converge
    if we let it
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/sony/ps4_mts.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/sony/ps4_mts.c
@@ -457,8 +457,62 @@
 	 * can do AN handshake via MDIO but cannot generate a link signal.
 	 * See mts_phy_pll_enable() comment + v85 result doc for the full
 	 * diagnosis.
+	 *
+	 * v86 hardware: PLL was already on - this is a no-op write but kept
+	 * for future hardware where the bootloader may not have set it.
 	 */
 	mts_phy_pll_enable(mts);
+
+	/*
+	 * v87: Orbis "unconditional tail" from mts_mac_init (post efuse-gated
+	 * block).  The 4-agent v87 dig (deepseek + kimi + gpt5.5 + glm) all
+	 * confirm these five C45 writes plus the C22 ANAR mask plus the BAR+0x04
+	 * mask are what Orbis literally does after the MAC register setup, and
+	 * we've been skipping them since v82.  Some of these writes target
+	 * Realtek vendor registers that are no-ops on MT7531, but `0x3c0007`
+	 * (MMD 7 reg 0x3c = ANEG-MMD) and the bit-clear in MMD 0x1e reg 0x330
+	 * could be load-bearing.
+	 */
+	{
+		u16 v16;
+
+		/* C45 unconditional tail writes (verbatim from Orbis decompile). */
+		mts_smi_c45_write(mts, 0x1e, 0x189, 0x110);
+		mts_smi_c45_write(mts, 0x1e, 0x122, 0xffff);
+		mts_smi_c45_write(mts, 0x1f, 0x268, 0x07f4);
+		mts_smi_c45_write(mts, 0x07, 0x03c, 0x0000);
+		if (mts_smi_c45_read(mts, 0x1e, 0x330, &v16) == 0) {
+			mts_smi_c45_write(mts, 0x1e, 0x330, v16 & ~0x1000);
+			dev_info(&mts->pdev->dev,
+				 "v87 tail: MMD 0x1e reg 0x330 0x%04x -> 0x%04x (cleared bit 12)\n",
+				 v16, v16 & ~0x1000);
+		}
+
+		/* C22 ANAR mask: clear bits 10-13 per Orbis. */
+		if (mts_smi_c22_read(mts, 0x04, &v16) == 0) {
+			mts_smi_c22_write(mts, 0x04, v16 & 0xf3ff);
+			dev_info(&mts->pdev->dev,
+				 "v87 tail: ANAR 0x%04x -> 0x%04x (mask 0xf3ff)\n",
+				 v16, v16 & 0xf3ff);
+		}
+
+		/* BAR+0x04 R/M/W mask: clear bits 8-9 + 12-13 + 31.  Orbis does
+		 * this TWICE in mts_mac_init (steps 34 and 47 per glm dig). */
+		writel(readl(bar + MTS_LINK_STATUS) & 0x7fffcfff,
+		       bar + MTS_LINK_STATUS);
+		(void)readl(bar + MTS_LINK_STATUS);
+		writel(readl(bar + MTS_LINK_STATUS) & 0x7fffcfff,
+		       bar + MTS_LINK_STATUS);
+		(void)readl(bar + MTS_LINK_STATUS);
+
+		/* Final AN restart per Orbis (BMCR |= 0x1200). */
+		if (mts_smi_c22_read(mts, 0x00, &v16) == 0) {
+			mts_smi_c22_write(mts, 0x00, v16 | 0x1200);
+			dev_info(&mts->pdev->dev,
+				 "v87 tail: BMCR 0x%04x -> 0x%04x (AN restart)\n",
+				 v16, v16 | 0x1200);
+		}
+	}
 }
 
 /*
@@ -734,17 +788,63 @@
 			}
 		}
 
+		/*
+		 * v87 diagnostic: read PHY reg 5 (LP ABILITY) and reg 10
+		 * (1000BT status) every iteration; log when they change.  Per
+		 * deepseek-v41: reg 5 bit 13 = REMOTE FAULT.  Per glm/RE doc:
+		 * reg 10 bit 13 = M/S config fault.  Watching these tells us
+		 * whether the partner keeps asserting RF or M/S resolution
+		 * is failing.
+		 */
+		{
+			u16 lpa = 0xffff, s1g = 0xffff;
+			static u16 prev_lpa = 0xffff, prev_s1g = 0xffff;
+
+			if (mts_smi_c22_read(mts, 0x05, &lpa) == 0 &&
+			    lpa != prev_lpa) {
+				dev_info(&mts->pdev->dev,
+					 "phy_ctrl: LP ABILITY (reg5)=0x%04x (RF=%d ACK=%d 100TX_FD=%d 100TX=%d 10T_FD=%d 10T=%d)\n",
+					 lpa,
+					 !!(lpa & 0x2000),
+					 !!(lpa & 0x4000),
+					 !!(lpa & 0x0100),
+					 !!(lpa & 0x0080),
+					 !!(lpa & 0x0040),
+					 !!(lpa & 0x0020));
+				prev_lpa = lpa;
+			}
+			if (mts_smi_c22_read(mts, 0x0a, &s1g) == 0 &&
+			    s1g != prev_s1g) {
+				dev_info(&mts->pdev->dev,
+					 "phy_ctrl: 1000BT_STAT (reg10)=0x%04x (MS_FAULT=%d MS_CFG=%d L_RX_OK=%d R_RX_OK=%d LP_FD=%d LP_HD=%d)\n",
+					 s1g,
+					 !!(s1g & 0x8000),
+					 !!(s1g & 0x4000),
+					 !!(s1g & 0x2000),
+					 !!(s1g & 0x1000),
+					 !!(s1g & 0x0800),
+					 !!(s1g & 0x0400));
+				prev_s1g = s1g;
+			}
+		}
+
 		if (!link_up) {
 			bool first = !mts->initial_an_done;
 			bool transition = was_up;
-			bool retry = (mts->link_down_iterations % 5) == 0
-				     && mts->link_down_iterations > 0;
-
-			if (first || transition || retry) {
+			/*
+			 * v87: REMOVED periodic AN restart.  v86 hardware showed
+			 * BMSR oscillating between 0x7949 / 0x7969 because we
